## Modern Web Guidance (Google Chrome team)

- Source: https://github.com/GoogleChrome/modern-web-guidance-src
- License: Apache License, Version 2.0 (see https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0)
- Copyright: Google LLC and Modern Web Guidance contributors

Methodology adapted (concept and vocabulary only — no verbatim code or prose):

- The closed-loop calibration pattern (paired gold-standard + negative
  fixtures; grader must pass on gold AND fail on negative) →
  `skills/skill-evaluator/references/calibration-loop.md`.
- The Playwright grader shape (paired `.spec.ts` over gold + negative
  HTML fixtures with inverted expectations; assertion targets across
  computed styles, accessibility tree, runtime behavior, and resource
  loading) → `skills/skill-evaluator/references/playwright-grader-shape.md`.
- The *opportunity* (`100% − unguided-pass-rate`) and *uplift*
  (`guided − unguided`) measurement vocabulary → cited in the
  `skills/ai-eval-review/SKILL.md` Influences callout and in
  `skills/skill-evaluator/references/calibration-loop.md`.

Modern Web Guidance is additionally cross-referenced (not absorbed)
from the team-composer Cross-Skill Integration table.

